node.text:
Dave Matthews @davematthewsband knows how to milk a billy goat and he has 35 elephants at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e) that adore him! Tune into hear his conversation with us to celebrate World Elephant Day! And watch our film Shaba, that he made the music for! We love you!!

#shabafilm #shaba #retetielephants @thephotosociety @passionplanet @nikonusa #elephants #stoppoaching #kenya #nikonlove #nikonambassador #nikonnofilter #conservation #amivitale #empathyiseverything

node.title: Dave Matthews Celebrates World Elephant Day With Reteti Elephant Sanctuary

node.text:
Film by @ronan_donovan. I am honored to be @TreadRight's first Wildlife Ambassador and thrilled to have made a new film with them featuring one of the places most near and dear to my heart, Montana's Centennial Valley. The film launches today on the @TreadRight feed. Don't miss it!.

Today, on World Ranger Day, more than 50 ranger teams across Africa are launching The Wildlife Ranger Challenge, an initiative to support over 7,000 men and women across Africa’s protected areas who are enduring drastic cuts in salaries and resources due to the devastating economic impact of Covid, and yet are still working tirelessly to safeguard the continent’s iconic wildlife.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
They will be competing in a 21K race on October 3rd. You can support them by doing your own 5, 10, or 21K run, walk or cycle or by taking the ranger quiz. A generous donor has offered to match funds raised which will be given to ranger teams in greatest need. Learn about the race and other ways you can support this critical initiate at wildliferangerchallenge.org
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Photos by @amivitale. Afghanistan is again under control by the Taliban, a name which means "students" of the Koran. In 1996, the Taliban declared an Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan and enforced the country with brutal public punishments and mass executions. They strictly restricted the roles of women, barring them from taking most jobs and even prohibiting girls from going to school. Today, after a U.S. led coalition spent twenty years fighting them, an estimated $2.2 trillion dollars, the Taliban are back ruling the country. It is important to know that the U.S. indirectly supported the Taliban through its ally in Pakistan between 1994 and 1996.  In the fight against the Soviet occupation of Afghanistan, the U.S. viewed the Taliban as anti-Iranian, anti-Shia and pro-Western. This legacy of repression and violence lives on in many Afghani's minds and today, many wait in fear to see if the Taliban will preserve the rights of women and "forgive" their enemies. As the Taliban takes power, there have been ample signs that those fears are well-grounded.

Follow these local organizations @parsa_afghanistan @womenforafghanwomen and international organizations - @mercycorps @careorg @womenforwomen @vitalvoices on the ground to learn more including how to help.

You can also donate directly to the Flyaway: Emergency Afghan Rescue Mission which is chartering planes to fly out people who otherwise have no chance at survival in the Taliban-occupied Kabul. (Link in profile)

 @thephotosociety #afghanistan #afghanwomen #taliban #peace

Photos by @amivitale. The Taliban have taken control of Afghanistan. How can we turn our backs on all the innocent human beings who will be targeted? I will be searching for ways we can help. This post from the @GeorgetownUniversity Institute for Women, Peace and Security at giwps.georgetown.edu/how-to-save-the-lives-of-afghan-women/ is a good place to start (link in profile.) In the meantime, we can support humanitarian visas, support those protecting those who spoke out and ask the U.S. government to make protecting women, minorities and activists a priority. 

@FastCompany has also written an article on getting involved. Go to fastcompany.com/90666326/how-to-help-afghanistan-things-you-can-do-right-now-for-a-country-in-crisis to help today. (Link in profile.)

Please follow these brave, thoughtful journalists. @afshinismaeli @lynseyaddario @andreabruce @stephsinclairpix @everydayafg, @pbbphoto, @argonautphoto @johnstanmeyer @yamashitaphoto @wakil.kohsar

Video by @amivitale. Dave Matthews (@davematthewsband) is serenaded by Samburu women visiting  @SararaCamp in northern Kenya. Dave has been an incredible supporter of the nearby @r.e.s.c.u.e elephant sanctuary. 

You can join him and help spread the word of how to help this magnificent community who are protecting elephants. For a limited time, your donations will be doubled. Another generous donor is matching donations up to $10,000.  My film Shaba will be screening until the end of the month and every ticket purchased is a direct donation to support the elephants and community at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e.) Watch now by going to shabafilm.org or click on the link in my profile.

And there's more incentive! Every person who tags a friend on my posts through the end of August and urges them to watch Shaba will be entered to win a signed 11x14 inch print of my photograph Elephants in the Mudhole. Every new tag = one entry, so share widely and let everyone know about the wonderful work @r.e.s.c.u.e does.

PS - Watch Dave's live call with @r.e.s.c.u.e on my IGTV now.

Photo by @amivitale. Join me in a couple of hours to speak with elephant keepers at @r.e.s.c.u.e for World Elephant Day (Aug. 12) it's already morning there so we will be speaking for the morning feeding of the babies at 1:30 am. Let's kick  off this special day with an @instagram Live with the team and their beautiful elephants!

If you miss that, I'm continuing the celebration throughout the whole day! Join us on a very special call with the musician @davematthewsband, at 10am EST on my Instagram account.

Later, tune in for an @Instagram Live hosted by Nikon at 3pm EST where I'll be discussing behind the scenes stories about the film I made called Shaba.

And at 5pm EST, sign in for an exclusive Make Travel Matter virtual event, from the @treadright, where we'll screen the film and I'll be taking your questions. (Link in profile).

The goal of all these events is to raise awareness about the sanctuary and provide much needed funding to help support it. Every ticket sold to view my new film through August 31 is a direct donation to Reteti. So, please set your alarms and spread the word far and wide.

node.text:
Photo by @amivitale. The divine Hamsini. Hamsini was rescued from a well when she was a year old in May 2019. She is cared for by the team at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e ) in northern Kenya. As the drought here continues, the dropping water table means that the wells are getting deeper and deeper. This makes it increasingly harder for elephants to get to the water and more likely for baby elephants like Hamsini to fall in and be orphaned. 

My new film "Shaba" tells the extraordinary story of Reteti's first matriarch. Ticket sales go directly to support orphaned elephants like Hamsini and her incredible keepers. It will be available on-demand until August 31. Visit shabafilm.org or click on the link in my profile to watch today.

#shabafilm #shaba #retetielephants@sandiegozoo @davematthewsband @thephotosociety @passionplanet @nikonusa #elephants #stoppoaching #kenya #nikonlove #nikonambassador #nikonnofilter #conservation #amivitale #empathyiseverything

Video by @amivitale. The orphans at Reteti drink 2 liter bottles of milk every three hours, around the clock. Each bottle is specially formulated for the particular nutritional needs of each baby elephant. In between feeds bottles are sterilized, the kitchen is cleaned and the next feed is prepared. All this is done while keeping a close eye on the elephants and showering them with love and care. The milk itself is sourced from the local community and its production is owned and managed by women, meaning it's both sustainably produced and supports both women's empowerment and the people who live here.

When you buy a ticket to see my new film, Shaba, you are buying a bottle of milk for one of these infants. 100% of ticket sales go directly to @r.e.s.c.u.e.  Your purchase ripples out, nourishing elephants and creating a brighter future for the community surrounding and caring for them. And now, thanks to a generous anonymous donor, the next $10,000 in contributions will be doubled. buying a ticket or by donating directly to @r.e.s.c.u.e. Visit shabafilm.org today and make a difference. A whole herd of elephants will thank you. Please share!!!

The wonderful and inspiring @jimmychin - Academy Award–winning director of Free Solo and @natgeo photographer - is publishing his first ever photography book - There and Back!!! 

It features his breathtaking portfolio of photographs, captured over twenty years during cutting-edge expeditions on all seven continents—from his early climbing trips to the Karakoram, skiing Mount Everest, to first ascents in Antarctica’s Queen Maud Land and never before seen images from Free Solo.
